# Contact form backend (Formspree).
# 1. Sign up at https://formspree.io and create a new form.
# 2. Copy the form's ID from its endpoint (https://formspree.io/f/XXXXXXXX → XXXXXXXX).
# 3. Copy this file to ".env" and paste the ID below, then restart `npm run dev`.
# If left unset, the contact form gracefully falls back to a mailto: link.
VITE_FORMSPREE_ID=mwvzdrow

# AI digital twin backend (Groq) — used by the /api/chat serverless function.
# Server-side only (NOT prefixed with VITE_, so it never reaches the browser).
# 1. Get a free key at https://console.groq.com/keys
# 2. Add GROQ_API_KEY in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# 3. For local testing of the function, put it here and run `vercel dev`
#    (plain `vite dev`/`vite preview` does NOT run /api functions).
# Optional: override the model (default: llama-3.3-70b-versatile).
GROQ_API_KEY=
# GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
